So we now have something
on Android Wear

00:27:29.430 --> 00:27:31.010
called direct connect.

00:27:31.010 --> 00:27:33.840
And the whole idea here is that
you can connect your Dexcom

00:27:33.840 --> 00:27:38.020
monitor to your Android Wear
device, without your phone.

00:27:38.020 --> 00:27:39.720
So, why is this really cool?

00:27:39.720 --> 00:27:42.430
So imagine that you're a kid in
school and you have diabetes.

00:27:42.430 --> 00:27:44.805
And you need to be checking
your blood sugar all the time

00:27:44.805 --> 00:27:46.690
to make sure that you stay safe.

00:27:46.690 --> 00:27:49.460
And you know before, you'd
have to look at your monitor

00:27:49.460 --> 00:27:50.180
all the time.

00:27:50.180 --> 00:27:52.180
Imagine being a kid and
you're pulling something

00:27:52.180 --> 00:27:54.264
out your pocket that looks
like this all the time.

00:27:54.264 --> 00:27:56.388
Other kids are probably
going to be looking at you,

00:27:56.388 --> 00:27:58.010
and you may or
may not want that.

00:27:58.010 --> 00:28:00.320
Or you could have it
connect to your phone.

00:28:00.320 --> 00:28:01.610
And that's definitely
better, and you're pulling

00:28:01.610 --> 00:28:02.859
your phone out of your pocket.

00:28:02.859 --> 00:28:05.080
That's a bit better, but
it's kind of a hassle.

00:28:05.080 --> 00:28:07.040
Maybe the teacher's wondering
if you're texting people.

00:28:07.040 --> 00:28:07.540
Right?

00:28:07.540 --> 00:28:09.710
So you want to have
something that's more subtle.

00:28:09.710 --> 00:28:11.930
And the best option
here is to just have

00:28:11.930 --> 00:28:13.251
it go directly to your watch.

00:28:13.251 --> 00:28:14.750
So you can just
glance at your watch

00:28:14.750 --> 00:28:16.400
as though you were
checking the time.

00:28:16.400 --> 00:28:18.899
And you can see if your blood
sugar is staying within range.

00:28:18.899 --> 00:28:20.144
That's really awesome.

00:28:20.144 --> 00:28:21.560
And it can allow
kids to do things

00:28:21.560 --> 00:28:24.300
that they might have felt a
little scared doing before.

00:28:24.300 --> 00:28:26.790
Like, if you have a
waterproof Android Wear watch,

00:28:26.790 --> 00:28:29.740
you can now use that to check
your blood sugar in the pool,

00:28:29.740 --> 00:28:30.791
without even getting out.

00:28:30.791 --> 00:28:31.290
Right?

00:28:31.290 --> 00:28:31.870
Wouldn't that be great?

